<item>
            <title>[JDK-8291302] ARM32: nmethod entry barriers support</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8291302</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>It is a time to implement nmethod entry barriers for ARM32. It have already been implemented in other ports. This becomes inevitable with the landing of Loom and &lt;a href=&quot;https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8290025&quot; title=&quot;Remove the Sweeper&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;JDK-8290025&quot;&gt;&lt;strike&gt;JDK-8290025&lt;/strike&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &amp;quot;Remove the Sweeper&amp;quot; which require nmethod entry barriers.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Nmethod entry barriers are needed for G1 concurrent marking to keep alive weak nmethod oop constants (see linked &lt;a href=&quot;https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8288970&quot; title=&quot;G1 does not keep weak nmethod oops alive&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;JDK-8288970&quot;&gt;&lt;strike&gt;JDK-8288970&lt;/strike&gt;&lt;/a&gt;). So it is a defect if they are missing.</description>
